  <Docs>
    <summary>Holds the arguments used to customize a typeface when creating a variation clone.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` is a `ref struct` that holds the arguments used to customize a
typeface when cloning it via <xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)>.
It allows you to specify variable font axis positions, a palette index, and per-entry
palette color overrides.

Because this is a `ref struct`, it cannot be stored on the heap. Create it on the stack,
configure its properties, and pass it directly to the `Clone` method.

## Examples

```csharp
SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate[] coords =
[
    new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"), Value = 700 },
];

var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    VariationDesignPosition = coords,
    PaletteIndex = 0,
};

using var variantFace = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
